usage: ./nth [-h] [[-]n] [file]

	h	Prints this help message.
	n	Line number to print, default to -1.
		Negative number prints from bottom.
	file	Input file, default to stdin.

examples:

	$ cat input | nth     # Print last line
	$ tail input | nth 2  # Print second line
	$ nth -3 input        # Third from the bottom
